title: Girls volleyball rankings for Oct. 18, 2015
text:
By Kyle Craig | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 18, 2015 6:15 PM 
There are only a couple tweaks to the lehighvalleylive girls volleyball rankings prior to the start of the postseason. 
Nazareth slides up a position after pulling off a dramatic five-set result against Central Catholic. 
Bethlehem Catholic also bumps up a place thanks to an Emmaus slide. 
The upcoming Eastern Pennsylvania Conference and District 11 tournaments provide plenty of chances for power shifts, but any change at the very top would need an outcome that completely shocks the state. 
Check out the full rankings by scrolling through the gallery atop this post.
